Subject: [PATCH 5/5] kms: Unlink outputs from unused connectors in
 update_outputs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fixes meta_output_kms_from_kms_connector returning a stale pointer to an
already-destroyed MetaOutputKms object after a monitor was disconnected.

Fixes: 863b31ca ("output/kms: Add meta_output_kms_from_kms_connector()")

v2:
* Handle it from update_outputs. (Jonas Ådahl)
v3:
* Rename to meta_unlink_kms_connector. (Jonas Ådahl)
* Always call meta_unlink_kms_connector first thing in the
  update_outputs loop. (Jonas Ådahl)
* Bail from meta_unlink_kms_connector if the quark isn't initialized yet
  (before the first time meta_output_kms_new is called), to avoid
  g_object_set_qdata logging a crtitical warning.

Part-of: <https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/mutter/-/merge_requests/4474>
---
 src/backends/native/meta-gpu-kms.c    |  2 ++
 src/backends/native/meta-output-kms.c | 11 +++++++++++
 src/backends/native/meta-output-kms.h |  2 ++
 3 files changed, 15 insertions(+)

